    <div class="article-content">
        <div class="sub-content-header">CEA's Gary Shapiro Encourages Consumer Technology Companies to Participate in Upcoming CE Week</div>
        <span class="smallText">Feb 25, 2011 05:09:04</span>
        
        <P>Innovation is our business.&nbsp;It is integral to the apps, services, content and products that our members create, boosting the economy, creating jobs, and making us safer, connected, entertained, educated and informed.&nbsp;<BR><BR>But innovation runs a year-round, 24/7 cycle.<BR><BR>That's why CEA is innovating as well with the launch of a mid-year 2011 plan to promote our industry, our new products and our achievements before a world audience during CEA's new CE Week in New York, June 20-24. It's simply the right place at the right time to prepare the media and trade for the all-important Q4 product launches and holiday messaging.&nbsp;CE Week is going to be an entirely new launch pad for your company. Just like other industries (ie, fashion) have aggregated their product line launches in New York, CE Week will grow, take over multiple venues, and create a convenient and collegial atmosphere for the media and trade to "take Manhattan" and tell our mid-year story to the world.&nbsp;There are already several great ways for your company to get started:</P>
<UL class=text>
<LI class=text>Join us at CEA Line Shows on 34th St. (June 22-23). It's CE Week Headquarters, so it'll be the primary traffic destination and meeting point, and our Digital Downtown Conference Chair Natali del Conte Morris is already recruiting an A-List of journalists to help out on the content. Last year the floor sold out, so act early on this one.</LI>
<LI class=text>We've expanded to an All-Suites Hotel (the Affinia Manhattan) on 7th Ave. (across from Penn Station) where we're hosting the CEA Demo Suites (June 21-22), home of a variety of residential technologies, home theater and audiophile demonstrations.&nbsp;Maureen Jensen of CustomRetailer is producing the conference program at this venue.</LI>
<LI class=text>Or you can do your own thing! The great part of CE Week is that it is infinitely customizable.&nbsp;There's simply no excuse not to participate.&nbsp;All official CE Week partner events benefit from central marketing, transportation and scheduling support. Using our industry’s own tools — social media, mobile electronics and the power of the web — we can stay connected during CE Week even though we're not in a single convention facility, and collectively, we can turn New York City into our industry's stage at this vital time of year.&nbsp; </LI></UL>
<P class=text>Join us in New York in June.&nbsp;Together we can innovate a new type of trade event and turn CE Week into our industry "mid-year showcase."<BR><BR>We hope to see you there!<BR><BR>Gary Shapiro<BR>President and CEO<BR>Consumer Electronics Association<BR></P>
    
